&gt; Oh yeah, undocumented code styles that may catch you are:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *         Use tabs instead of spaces
&gt;
&gt; *         If you optimize imports, make sure that the java.* classes
&gt; come before the remainder of imports
&gt;
&gt; *         Place static imports last
&gt;
&gt; *         Assignments are &quot;variable= value&quot; (notice no space between =
&gt; and the variable, but a space between = and the value)
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; This will help avoid having to resend patches.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; From: junit@yahoogroups.com &lt;mailto:junit%40yahoogroups.com&gt;
